content.description: Coming out of the wide crack and pressing up onto a great ledge. Up on more small hand crack then walk up to a tree anchor. Rappel off left side slabs. Best
content.protection: #1-#5 cams, anchor system needed for TR. Tree anchor
content.location: On the right section of Eastbound wall 40ft to the left of Old Soldiers.

content.description: Getting above the third bolt is the crux. Stay to the left of the third bolt try not to sweat.
content.location: Right side of the Eastbound wall.

content.description: Start in a high corner. (Good belay spot) up and over first ledge then start up cracks with small good foot ledge. Up onto a great ledge then, climbing left into a chimney with a chockstone up over that Â 20ft back there are 2 anchor bolts with chain links hanging. Good for rappel.
content.location: Walking up to Eastbound wall Right you can see obvious bolts on lower slab face climbs. Looking to the left (North) you may start to see anchors bolts and a few places on the south and west facing cliffs. About 15 recorded climbs on this left portion of the Eastbound wall
